<paragraph blockId="39.[136,1452,1345,1588]" pageId="39" pageNumber="250">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,294,1382,1408]" pageId="39" pageNumber="250">Notes:—</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Luer" authorityYear="1982" baseAuthorityName="Luer" baseAuthorityYear="1979" box="[294,524,1382,1408]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="39" pageNumber="250" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="uxorius">
<emphasis box="[294,524,1382,1408]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="250">Myoxanthus uxorius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is caespitose with narrow leaves generally with revolute margins and yellowish glabrous flowers that are similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fraga &amp; Kollmann" authorityYear="2003" box="[532,647,1418,1444]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="39" pageNumber="250" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ruschii">
<emphasis box="[532,647,1418,1444]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="250">M. ruschii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[714,785,1418,1444]" name="Brazil" pageId="39" pageNumber="250">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, but 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Luer" authorityYear="1982" baseAuthorityName="Luer" baseAuthorityYear="1979" box="[839,960,1419,1444]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="39" pageNumber="250" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="uxorius">
<emphasis box="[839,960,1419,1444]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="250">M. uxorius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinguished by its unmottled sepals and petals 
<emphasis box="[208,231,1455,1480]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="250">vs</emphasis>
. darkly mottled, column foot without calli 
<emphasis box="[711,734,1455,1480]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="250">vs</emphasis>
. with a pair of thick calli near the apex, yellow lip suffused with brown, obovate arcuate, convex above the middle, the disc with a pair of smooth, rounded calli bellow the middle 
<emphasis box="[1421,1444,1491,1516]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="250">vs</emphasis>
. reddish to brownish, obovate, with angled elevated margin near the middle and revolute slightly verrucose margins above the middle.
</paragraph>
